**	<Erodix> theres one little thing.. when psycle is playing and i double-click an song, a new
	psycle opens..
	[ DDE ? mmmm... ]
<Ksh>
Can someone at last do something with the little disturbing behaviour of opening new Psycle instances for files opened from the command line? If DDE is too complex then you could implement something very simple and still effective:
- when Psycle runs, it pops a mutex
- when another instance is launched, it sees that there is already one opened because there is already a mutex
- then it passes the command line arguments to the first instance by throwing a windows message and exits
- the first one receives the message and optionally asks user: "Save changes?", and then opens the new file
Isn't that simple?

